text.tspan: An agent review function: The agent Mb reviews the
contents of source Ma, internalizing its contents,
thereby updating the agent mode. The state of the

A model object: models are structured information
A source model object: sources are releasable.
A release is a static configuration of the object.
An autonomous agent: capable of interpreting
Current functional state of a model, serves as
a go/nogo gate for downstream functions depending
A strange loop: An agent uses a definition model to
produce a build, the build is executed, which
updates the build model and produces a build state.
The agent uses the build state and updated model to
reassess and update the definition model. The process
may repeat an arbitrary number of iterations.
